#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:28
msgid "Subtitle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:35
msgid ""
"The subtitling tool allows you to add and edit subtitles directly in the "
"timeline on a special subtitle track or by using the new subtitle window. "
"You can also import (**SRT**/**ASS**) and export (**SRT**) subtitles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:38
msgid "3 ways to add subtitle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:40
msgid "**Menu**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:42
msgid ":menuselection:`Project --> Subtitle --> Add Subtitle`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:44
msgid "**Keyboard**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:46
msgid ":kbd:`Shift + S` adds a subtitle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:48
msgid "**Icon and Mouse**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:50
msgid ""
"Click :guilabel:`Add Subtitle` icon in the :ref:`timeline_toolbar` to open "
"the subtitle track in the timeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:51
msgid "Double-click in the subtitle track to add a subtitle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:52
msgid ""
"Click :guilabel:`Add Subtitle` in the :ref:`timeline ruler <timeline_ruler>` "
"context menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:55
msgid "Adding and editing text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:57
msgid ""
"Add or editing text either directly into the subtitle clip or in the "
"subtitle window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:60
msgid "Adjust the length of subtitle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:62
msgid ""
"Grab the end of a subtitle with the mouse and lengthen or shorten it as "
"needed. Set subtitle in/out can be achieved with the same shortcut as to set "
"clip in/out (left/right parenthesis shortcut)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:69
msgid "Split subtitle after first line"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:73
msgid ""
"With this feature, you can cut the selected subtitle with the Razor-Tool, "
"after the first line of the current track position. The first line becomes "
"the left subtitle before the track position, and the rest becomes the right "
"subtitle after the track position. It then selects the right-hand subtitle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:79
msgid ""
"To enable this feature go to :menuselection:`Settings --> Configure "
"Kdenlive... --> Tools` switch to :guilabel:`Split after first line`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:85
msgid ""
"Select the subtitle in the timeline that contains two lines. Click on the "
"subtitle with the Razor-Tool (X)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:91
msgid "Subtitle after you have split it with the Razor-Tool"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:93
msgid ""
"This makes it easier to split up subtitles, where you have a transcription "
"with one subtitle per line. This comes from a couple of situations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:95
msgid "You have put the audio through an external transcription service"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:97
msgid "You are adding subtitles to a song that you have the lyrics for"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:102
msgid "Subtitle window"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:107
msgid ""
"The subtitles window allows easier editing and also makes it possible to "
"easily navigate between subtitles with the :guilabel:`Left` and :guilabel:"
"`Right` buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:108
msgid "With the plus sign button, you can add subtitles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:109
msgid ""
"The scissors are mostly here for divide subtitles: let's say your subtitle "
"text is too long and you want to make it 2 different subtitles. Put the "
"cursor in the text widget where you want to cut and click the scissors, it "
"will split the text between 2 different subtitle items. The scissors are "
"only working when the playhead is over the subtitle itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:110
msgid "The tick button adds the text to the subtitle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:113
msgid "Style subtitle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:120
msgid ""
"This is a global, simple subtitle styling possibility. It only allows one "
"style for all subtitles of the project. Accessible through the \"T drop\" "
"icon in the subtitle edit widget."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:124
msgid ""
"**SRT** supports markup for: bold, italic, underline, text color and line "
"break."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:126
msgid "``<b>text in boldface</b>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:127
msgid "``<i>text in italics</i>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:128
msgid "``<u>text underlined</u>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:129
msgid ""
"``<font color=\"#00ff00\"> text in green</font>`` you can use the font tag "
"only to change color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:130
msgid ""
"And all combined: ``<font color=\"#00ff00\"><b><i><u>All combined</u></i></"
"b></font>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:131
msgid ""
"**Line break:** Add on the end of each line a ``<br>`` (for break). Now the :"
"file:`.srt` file is stored correct and reopened with the line break. The "
"subtitle in the subtitle window will be all in 1 line after several save but "
"the breaks is working."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:133
msgid ":kbd:`Alt + arrow` jumps from subtitle to subtitle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:137
msgid "Import and export subtitle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:141
msgid "Allows importing .vtt (Web Video Text Tracks) and .sbv (YouTube) files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:143
msgid ""
"Importing **SRT**, **ASS**, **VTT** and **SBV** subtitle file: :"
"menuselection:`Project --> Subtitles --> Import Subtitle File`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:145
msgid ""
"Exporting **SRT** subtitles only: :menuselection:`Project --> Subtitles --> "
"Export Subtitle File`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:154
msgid ""
"Allow overriding of detected codecs through a list of available codecs, and "
"show a preview to make choice easier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:158
msgid "Spelling check"
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/subtitle.rst:162
msgid ""
"Spelling check for subtitle is integrated and shows incorrect words by a red "
"wiggly line. Right-click on the word and you get a list of possible words "
"you can choose by click on it."
msgstr ""
